commit_message:
Allow 'openstack baremetal configure boot' to guess the root device

This change simplifies using Ironic root device hints for people who only need
to change the default strategy of selecting the default device.
E.g. we have a use case for selecting the first device instead of the smallest,
so that the root device does not change after upgrade Kilo -> Liberty.

Note that this feature does not replace per-node device hints, rather
complement them with a more global and easy to use setting.

This change introduces 3 new arguments to the command:
--root-device states how to find a root devices for a node.
  If this argument is provided, the client will try to detect the root device
  based on the stored introspection data. Possible values:
  * smallest (the same thing as IPA does by default - the smallest device)
  * largest (the opposite thing - pick the largest device)
  * otherwise it's treated as a comma-separated list of possible device names,
    e.g. sda,vda,hda rouchly matches the logic the Kilo ramdisk used.
  The resulting device WWN or serial (whatever is available) is then recorded
  in the root device hints (/properties/root_device) for a node.
--root-device-minimum-size minimum size of the considered devices
  The default value of 4 GiB matches what IPA does.
--overwrite-root-device-hints allows overwriting root device hints set
  previously. It's disabled by default to allow more precise control over the
  root device for some subset of nodes.

Note that for these arguments to work, this command should be run after
introspection. A separate documentation change will be posted for that.

Change-Id: I9f19554c5e7f34c8f63c1603c32b4d470fb12592

commit_message:
Node list permits individual and group selection.

This patch enables the checkboxes in the node list, as well as
the selectAll checkbox in the title. Data is stored in
controller.selectedNodes, and automatically update based on user
action.

Note that this patch uses the somewhat inefficient $watch and
$watchCollection methods. Care should be taken not to overload
these methods to prevent inifinite event loops.

Change-Id: I71872e5c080a9b230d6ac086aee9f1e0c9ad492c

The following fixes/enhancements were made to commands.py:

- fixed issue where 'complete' generated wrong subcommands
  if they were hyphenated.
- added flag to contiunue processing clients even if an error
  occurs.
- fixed issue where deprecated options caused the entire
  command to be skipped.
- added ability to supply multiple clients at a time.
- fixed issue where an empty file was created if the client
  wasn't found.
- fixed issue where 'hardcoded' subcommands (in clients.yaml)
  were ignored.

Tested the results on most of the clients.  There are still
some issues outstanding (i.e. the 'openstack' client still
isn't handled correctly) but these can be addressed later.

Change-Id: I621e9d64b5f72530014c47a281e837eeeb800987

commit_message:
Use new style form templates

This patch addresses two bugs by updating to the new style form
template.

By using the new style form the standard horizon common form is
used for the footer and fixes the issue where the cancel button
has the wrong font size.

It also fixes the gate issue where there was a failing test due
to the url not being accessible.  Updating to the new style form
with the url as a view attribute fixes that issue.

Added code in the views to populate the new standard form
attributes.

Removed the code in the old style form templates
and used the new style.

Removed some unneeded icon attributes in the grow/shrink
table actions.

Added some code to suppress the output of expected exceptions in
the tests.

Change-Id: If04f24d46c251079bcbe232b94eaee4f30c73ed3
Closes-Bug: #1566506
Closes-Bug: #1568876
(cherry picked from commit 43602654eb7bea4d4aaee1d9d65ded2af96e6104)

[{'account_id': 21408, 'date': '2016-04-14 08:49:46.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 10068, 'date': '2016-04-14 08:50:01.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code

commit_message:
Updated role using the Multi-Distro framework

* The default apt packages have been moved into a var file
  that is only loaded when the detected OS is matched.
* The Install task file has had the apt specific tasks moved
  into a named install task file.

Change-Id: I0b31d5d76d3aaedf3b87550165d0e670b314bebd

commit_message:
Centos gives /dev/pts/ptmx the wrong perms

In order to use cinder, we need to be able to use
/dev/pts/ptmx.  Centos sets this to 000 when on Fedora
it's 666.

Closes-bug: #1564477
Change-Id: I76dc5adc64d2da0d27204ea31175244bc1b94428
(cherry picked from commit d2710b871b9f0141f0e7150590f896ab1fd71ba7)

commit_message:
Add final success/failure message to ping test

The actual result of the ping test is about halfway through the
output of the test, and the DONE message at the end is not all
that meaningful since the test should never not complete.  This
change replaces that message with a more specific one based on the
exitval variable.

Change-Id: Ib6deeb87b975c87c3269958ad88c0d0991b42828

commit_message:
Change logic of checking failure message

- In case failure message isn't present in Astute
we fail with list index out of range in
deploy_cluster_with_reboot_plugin_timeout so change logic of check

Change-Id: I93831209401ad0a2757779baf17c24fa7da60b4c
Closes-Bug: #1564991

commit_message:
Added ensure_resource for python-memcache package.

python-memcache package is required for memcache backend
if horizon is configured to use memcache for backend.

Change-Id: I74a97ad2f220bdf88718086815f8f8db54a17f30
Closes-Bug: 1556132
(cherry picked from commit e0a67d63eba6d551f650f56c105aaf4a99efcc49)

commit_message:
Support the LibreSwan driver in Red Hat platforms

Currently, the libreswan package is supported by puppet-neutron as
part of the openswan driver. However, there is a specific libreswan
driver, which is required when using it (see
https://bugs.launchpad.net/neutron/+bug/1444017 for details).

Adding support for the LibreSwan driver in puppet-neutron, only for
Red Hat platforms as it does not seem to be supported in Debian/Ubuntu.

Change-Id: I9628e485d301734f9d739c1d03d6da9f7887c61d
(cherry picked from commit f6c48bb76c95fe09e05f24fc4437d20fdb5230d2)

commit_message:
Add ml2 package requirement to neutron::plugins::ml2::mech_driver

In certain scenarios the neutron::plugins::ml2::mech_driver was being
executed before the $::neutron::params::ml2_server_package which
caused problems while trying to write plugin files.

Change-Id: I31fa00030201b86baca14f9cb3bccab91c593e85
(cherry picked from commit 2b4cba7c87bcb46d3b5c9919948f03bbc33a6a0b)

[{'created': '2016-04-18 20:08:49.000000000', 'message': 'Remove NM on Fuel Master, fix dhclient-enter-hooks

This patch blocks NetworkManager and dhclient from modifying
/etc/resolv.conf.

NetworkManager overwrites /etc/resolv.conf, occasionally
breaking local node resolution. l23network module will remove
it cleanly.

After upgrade to CentOS7, the proper script for DHCP hook disabling
is /etc/dhcp/dhclient-enter-hooks, which is now renamed.

Change-Id: I9bf6a4ce2f59f320cc1681fe108da3dd4de70ed9
Closes-Bug: #1567957
(cherry picked from commit 0717a769afdd8fff0b120f570a0d03a91c8c2be9)
'}]
commit_message:
Remove NM on Fuel Master, fix dhclient-enter-hooks

This patch blocks NetworkManager and dhclient from modifying
/etc/resolv.conf.

NetworkManager overwrites /etc/resolv.conf, occasionally
breaking local node resolution. l23network module will remove
it cleanly.

After upgrade to CentOS7, the proper script for DHCP hook disabling
is /etc/dhcp/dhclient-enter-hooks, which is now renamed.

Change-Id: I9bf6a4ce2f59f320cc1681fe108da3dd4de70ed9
Closes-Bug: #1567957
(cherry picked from commit 0717a769afdd8fff0b120f570a0d03a91c8c2be9)

commit_message:
Fail fast when required secrets are not present

Required variables that are secrets (i.e. passwords and keys) are validated as
present before any part of the role executes.

Change-Id: I91a7130005101006bb219f2911b4c38626786908

commit_message:
Angular vs. Django Table Danger Button Inconsistency

A button should have either btn-default OR btn-danger ... not both.

This also removes the flashing red change this  problem caused when
adding a 'disabled' class to the button after its already been
rendered on the page.

Closes-bug: #1557729
Closes-bug: #1549957

Change-Id: I6e035868be4df653438b4d31b462729c3fe06d9f

commit_message:
Add a reload of keepalived

When SSL is enabled on the undercloud, during an upgrade, os-net-config
might restart network interfaces. This will cause keepalived to not
be able to keep the VIPs it controls up. The reload of the keepalived
gives it a chance to add the VIPs back where they should be.

Change-Id: Id4b1dbdd976bce0a157a16e1bd47033dbfca8675
Closes-Bug: #1570824

commit_message:
Fail fast when required secrets are not present

Required variables that are secrets (i.e. passwords and keys) are validated as
present before any part of the role executes.

Change-Id: I37f25c6c5bcc0b4df8cf8ccc8018663fe7ca9817

commit_message:
Send remote restart to neutron plugin post upgrade

When this principle charm performs and Openstack upgrade the
subordinates packages are also upgraded. The subordinate may need
to render new config for the new release so the charm now sends a
restart trigger to the subordinate

Change-Id: Ifd5dea4e67d09dc29bb0bba579fd8903fb64490a
Partial-Bug: 1571634

commit_message:
Decrease MariaDB wait timeout

This MariaDB setting uses the same timeout for SQL connections
as configured inside SQL Alchemy (pool_recycle) and prevent possibly
SQL session build up due to a large default setting (8 Hours).

Nova and Neutron are using a idle_timeout of 3600 by default,
for example
https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/db/sqlalchemy/api.py#L101
and respectively for Neutron
https://github.com/openstack/neutron/blob/stable/liberty/etc/neutron.conf#L761

Change-Id: I273739c3c10616cac148aeb839154e0fb3359bca
Closes-Bug: #1571682

[{'created': '2016-04-13 18:23:58.000000000', 'message': 'Add options to auto enable VPNaaS

This change makes it possible for the neutron role to enable VPNaaS using
the reference OpenSwan driver by simply setting the `vpnaas` option within
the **neutron_plugin_base** list. This capability has been within the role
for some time however never specifically configured.

The change will bind the vpnaas agent to any location that is within the
neutron_l3_agent group. The agnet brings with it a new ini file and a new
entry point for config_template overrides. The vpnaas packages will be
installed when the agent is enabled within the target location of the
running agent services.

Change-Id: Ie9f89f7d2a942df40841d72c82f3a34315c6bed9
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Add options to auto enable VPNaaS

This change makes it possible for the neutron role to enable VPNaaS using
the reference OpenSwan driver by simply setting the `vpnaas` option within
the **neutron_plugin_base** list. This capability has been within the role
for some time however never specifically configured.

The change will bind the vpnaas agent to any location that is within the
neutron_l3_agent group. The agnet brings with it a new ini file and a new
entry point for config_template overrides. The vpnaas packages will be
installed when the agent is enabled within the target location of the
running agent services.

Change-Id: Ie9f89f7d2a942df40841d72c82f3a34315c6bed9
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

Added horizon documentation section for cinder

deployers learn how to override the default horizon behavior with OSA.

Closes-Bug: #1518845

[{'created': '2016-04-15 13:49:39.000000000', 'message': 'Improved documentation about LVM overwrite behaviour

commit_message:
Doc: Improved documentation about LVM overwrite behaviour

LVM configuration is overwritten on nodes part of the hosts group.
This documentation explains that behaviour to a deployer, because
he may not think at first sight that its LVM configuration could
be overwritten in hosts others than the cinder ones.

Change-Id: I82769250f057bac28385cf63c8e1df7c7df511f5
Closes-Bug: #1488532

commit_message:
Adding modularity to keepalived configuration

This patch introduces modularity into the default keepalived
configuration: Currently, keepalived uses a ping to check its
alive status. The IP was hard setted in the configuration file.

This patch introduces multiple variables:
- keepalived_ping_address
- keepalived_ping_count
- keepalived_ping_interval

The one probably used the most will be the
``keepalived_ping_address``. It's therefore listed in
``user_variables`` with the other keepalived variables.

Fixes-Bug: #1570420

Change-Id: Ic9a591fe739dd4ee3b0ad0130190e000404fb73a

commit_message:
Explicitly set num_engine_workers for mitaka and below

Since the num_engtine_workers paramter was added [1] in Newton, we
still need to set this parameter for mitaka and below. So we do so by
having a separate environment for those branches.

[1] I69565c13b732ef74531a516aac8a368597411856

Change-Id: I2d9a0ac739b3ee5becdd844640d5e3daee3611e8

Rename block-device -> block-devices

Add support for block-devices, but still only accept one block device.

Add tests for parsing the device block list.

Change-Id: I78fe3b9e617a7da75145a2695bee312cf3685246

commit_message:
Update determine_packages to let package dependencies win

A previous charm work-around for forcefully installing the
mysql-client-5.6 package is no longer relevant, with
Utopic and Vivid both EOL.  Wily and Xenial package
dependencies are in order for mysql-client.

Change-Id: I6d8c0c34d3bb3c4d19b641086f70c197961c4ad4
Closes-Bug: 1571789
Related-Bug: 1476845

commit_message:
Give cinder time to create volume

Avoid error trying to use volume before create is done:
volume 'xxx' status must be 'available'. Currently in 'in-use'

Change-Id: I30231c6bfb30de07685ad2136fce18595302eac2

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be

commit_message:
Updated retrieval of 'id' in objects/plugins.py

When updating a Fuel plugin which is the new format, the json response
contains 'id' at the root of the json response.
To support the old format I've updated code to retrieve 'id' from the
'message' object.

Closes-Bug: #1565883

Change-Id: Ie411ef322fa9ebc5887fef9db53d4318b99ae857

commit_message:
Fix get_deployment_mode to rely on keys directory

Docker is no longer used, so this is a way to tell if
the system was deployed and block changing risky settings.

Change-Id: Ic78a973ca7e9f16b1f32c98f15f736993615e859
Closes-Bug: #1567300

commit_message:
Fixes icon font paths

The icon font path overrides contained a trailing slash, which resulted
in a double slash in the final font URLs.

Change-Id: Idc26379b0393c35f58292f9ffe626625371a46d0

(5 comments)

So I realize I'm giving some conflicting advice from ian, however I do think we should just put this stuff in /usr/local because I'm concerned about other path issues in openstack that assume install locations for these tools (like qemu-info, which is called a lot in Nova)."}, {'account_id': 2750, 'date': '2014-09-29 15:24:18.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7: Code-Review-1'}, {'account_id': 1779, 'date': '2014-09-29 15:33:11.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7:

If we use /usr/local then you can only easily install one version of libvirt/QEMU at a time per machine. When people are testing with non-distro versions, it is reasonable that they might want to have different versions on the same machine, eg to try to debug & identify behavioural differences between 2 versions of libvirt or QEMU.

By using the devstack $DEST directory they can setup multiple devstack configs, each with different versions of libvirt/QEMU on the same machine, without conflicts.

If there are places in Nova which hardcode absolute paths to thing like qemu-img we should fix them to honour $PATH for locating the binaries. NB, libvirt will look at $PATH when locating QEMU already'}, {'account_id': 1779, 'date': '2014-09-29 15:42:12.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7: Code-Review-1

I'm afraid to bring not so good news: unlike previous patch versions (e.g. patch set #9) on Fedora 21, this patch set fails to use the newly compiled QEMU correctly. I tested this twice locally on Fedora 21 and this problem manifests more than once. Michele acknowledged on IRC that he tested this only on Ubuntu:

Failed test
-----------

With:

  $ egrep 'QEMU_VERSION|LIBVIRT_VERSION' local.conf 
  QEMU_VERSION=2.2.0
  LIBVIRT_VERSION=1.2.11

once successful DevStack completes and booting a Nova picks up old (system provided) QEMU binary:

  $ /usr/bin/qemu-system-x86_64

  $ ps -ef | grep qemu-system-x86_64
  root     19217     1  0 09:15 ?        00:00:04 /usr/bin/qemu-system-x86_64 -machine accel=kvm -name instance-00000001 [. . .]

However, the newly built qemu-system-x86_64 binaries are placed in 

  $  /usr/local/bin/qemu-system-x86_64

So, placing the newly compiled QEMU binary (qemu-system-x86_64) in /usr/bin/ should resolve the issue in this case."}, {'account_id': 6962, 'date': '2015-01-12 15:19:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 12: -Code-Review

You see that error if you try to perform guest vCPU pinning in TCG mode.

The exact error comes from this recent commit from upstream libvirt

  http://libvirt.org/git/?p=libvirt.git;a=commitdiff;h=65686e5a81d654d834d338fceeaf0229b2ca4f0d -- disable vCPU pinning with TCG mode

As the commit message explains, this is disabled explicitly in TCG,

"
[. . .]
Since few people will care about the performance of TCG with strict CPU pinning, lets just disable that for now [. . .]
"'}, {'account_id': 1779, 'date': '2015-02-06 11:43:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 13:

It is fundamentally impossible to test CPU pinning with TCG (aka plain QEMU) because TCG only has a single thread for all virtual CPUs. As such there is no mechanism to pin vCPU threads with TCG.  Nested KVM is thus the only possible option for testing any of the NUMA / CPU pinning stuff. Instructions for nested KVM setup on a KVM host are documented here

[{'created': '2014-07-22 14:54:52.000000000', 'message': "Support for qemu and libvirt custom git repositories

The user can now define the variables(local.conf):
- LIBVIRT_REPO and LIBVIRT_BRANCH for libvirt
- QEMU_REPO and QEMU_BRANCH for qemu

to enable the compilation and the installation of libvirt and
qemu from git repositories.

LIBVIRT_PY_REPO and LIBVIRT_PY_BRANCH are required when LIBVIRT_REPO
is set, because the installation of the libvirt-python's
dependencies from the OS package manager may conflict with
the compiled libvirt.

Change-Id: I89d20609fbfc8791892ab103c7b25c1334e3e94d
Signed-off-by: Michele Paolino <m.paolino@virtualopensystems.com>
"}, {'created': '2014-07-28 11:15:15.000000000', 'message': 'Support for libvirt/QEMU tar releases

Enable to install libvirt and QEMU from tar releases.
Defining the variables LIBVIRT_URL, LIBVIRT_PY_URL and QEMU_URL will
result in the compilation and the installation of libvirt and
QEMU from the tar files linked in the variables.

local.conf example:
QEMU_URL=http://wiki.qemu-project.org/download/qemu-2.1.0-rc3.tar.bz2
LIBVIRT_URL=http://libvirt.org/sources/libvirt-1.2.6.tar.gz
LIBVIRT_PY_URL=http://libvirt.org/sources/python/libvirt-python-1.2.6.tar.gz

commit_message:
Support for libvirt/QEMU tar releases

Enable to install libvirt and QEMU from tar releases.
The definition of the variables LIBVIRT_VERSION and QEMU_VERSION
will result in the compilation and the installation of libvirt and
QEMU from the tar releases pointed in the variables.

local.conf example:
QEMU_VERSION=2.2.0
LIBVIRT_VERSION=1.2.12

Change-Id: I89d20609fbfc8791892ab103c7b25c1334e3e94d

commit_message:
Use PortOpt instead of IntOpt for port configurations

Since PortOpt in oslo.config is available, we should use this for ports.
Port configurations changed in this patch:

ec2_listen_port
osapi_compute_listen_port
metadata_listen_port

Change-Id: I961db383b6b39ea055a5e2d7fb44fcc99c708068

commit_message:
Add upgrade ceph osd command

This command required for upgrade all osds on compute in one moment.
If they are in wrong version of osd on computes it breaks osd cluster.

usage:

octane upgrade-osd --admin-password $password $ORIG_ID

Change-Id: I0b8199ef2f4d39541afa39f5543d4863f28517f0
Blueprint: upgrade-cluster-7-to-8
(cherry picked from commit f66bb89093bef781aa1318aab0afc310a2360b0f)

commit_message:
Hide the postci logs

If ci fails early in the run and as a results some resources
are not ready for postci to access them then error messages are
generated that have nothing to do with the root cause of the
problem. Pipe postci error messages to a file so that they don't
get confused with the actual error.

Change-Id: I9ca394d17d76f701d7a4fe0f19f61fd0747cf46d

commit_message:
Make task version check in lcm serializer optional

The option LCM_CHECK_TASK_VERSION will control
task serializer allows to start deploy with tasks
that have version less than 2.0.0 or not.

Change-Id: I452c91b8343bf2a77b037920d924238c0a851ba1
Closes-Bug: 1570973

commit_message:
* Fixed debian/gbp.conf
* Fixed parsing of the GPG pub key ID
* Checkout the packaging branch before doing gbp buildpackage
* Updated debian/changelog
* Added "newgrp - sbuild" when building packages.
* Using ssh to localhost to start "gbp buildpackage" to work around the sbuild relogins problem.

Change-Id: If092b9877917baf2444588ad2b4069cc8c8c8178

commit_message:
Migrated auth system from keystoneclient to keystoneauth

Changes:

 * added keystoneauth to requirements
 * changed imports in clients.py module
 * changed mock.patch decorators in test_init_clients in test_base.py

bp migrate-to-keystoneauth
Change-Id: Ie731dc87fc1306a4aafcfdcd7d73b1723a95092a

I would like to minimize the differences between the two network APIs here if possible.  The easy one is for Compute to accept --long, suppress in help and ignore it.

Is it possible (or even desirable) for the Network API to list only current rules by default and use --all-projects to get the current behaviour?'}, {'account_id': 8276, 'date': '2016-04-13 09:38:25.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

neutron API return all project's resource by default, if caller have admin role, that's different with other projects(nova, cinder), I prefer to only list the current project resource by default, then if all_projects is specified, list all resource.

I'm curious what's others thought?"}, {'account_id': 8410, 'date': '2016-04-13 16:09:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Thanks for the review Dean and Rui.  

I'll update Compute v2 to accept --long but suppress its help and ignore it.

Filtering based on the admin role may be tricky and I'm not sure it's desirable... thinking about keystone configuration, neutron policy files, etc.  I didn't find a related option on the Network API.  So I would prefer to leave all of the network command objects behaving the same and take what the API gives us for now.  If you'd like, I could open a blueprint to continue investigating this behavior further across all OSC commands.

I should have noted that my intention with the --all-projects option was to align the "security group rule list" command with the "security group list" command which has the option but suppress its help and ignores it for Network v2.  For consistency, I'll do the same.'}, {'account_id': 8410, 'date': '2016-04-13 16:56:30.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2016-04-13 18:04:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified+1

commit_message:
Add options to security group rule list

Add the following options to the 'os security group rule list'
command:
  --long: Display direction and ethertype for Network v2
  --all-projects: Display information from all projects for Compute v2

Change-Id: If8a1cbd7669cdfa6577d6d2f6fffd9e999a39a82
Partial-Bug: #1519512
Implements: blueprint neutron-client

commit_message:
Temporarily remove policy configuration

We need to temporarily remove the policy configuration for aodh so it
can be correctly moved to the upstream.  This change will be a
depends-on for the upstream change so we don't break deployments
accidently.

Change-Id: I4e24d49ed7e84a3b5cb991e912ed320c393569e4
Closes-Bug: #1570109

commit_message:
Update puppet-pacemaker to 1.0.6 tag

Commit 8780696d6f1367f1a3b3c0ef737a89167e61732e disables
checking/disabling upstart service provider for services
during stop/status, leaving it only for the "start"
command. This prevents the pacemaker service provider
from stopping RabbitMQ via upstart and then starting
it immediately via pacemaker.

Change-Id: Ifc0a98aace537e59df089a5e8b287847052f6dc7
Closes-Bug: #1565840

commit_message:
Don't use caching in stable jobs

Currently we maintain a single image cache, it should only be used when
running jobs on master branch, to prevent mixing different releases
together.

Change-Id: I8c206ae3a6f732c8532f37a844ce2e96234087d2

commit_message:
Add audit-template name checking in CLI

This patch set allows to send audit_template_uuid as uuid type only.
If audit_template argument given as name, watcherclient will send request
to get audit template uuid.

Change-Id: Idf5f07ca08f2e5d871dc2163c32fbda9ed338a99

commit_message:
Remove fake root hierarchy level values

We don't really need them, they can be represented by parent_id=None in
their childs. This prevents race condition in flat environment (with
only "nodes" level), added comments about how to properly fix race
condition.

TODO: check that migration and code work on real environment

Closes-bug: 1569353
Change-Id: I16740b006b8276f01504eb95997319ab610dfe1c

commit_message:
Select Thierry Carrez as TC chair for Newton

The chair is responsible for making sure meetings are held
according to the rules described in our charter, and for
communicating the decisions taken during those meetings to the
Board of Directors and the OpenStack community at large.

If you'll have me, I'll be happy to serve again this cycle.
If you'd like to submit your own candidacy, please propose
an alternate patch. We'll vote on this at the next meeting.

Change-Id: I23f8953f510b2ec8bf4ab9def49891e2ebc2cc1e

commit_message:
Add last commit info to short-report output

Example output:

commit_message:
Remove explicit 'cluster' argument from UpdateOpenstackConfigTask

"cluster" argument for method UpdateOpenstackConfigTask.message
is redudnant, since it can be retrieved from "task.cluster".
It also causes TypeError when trying to call method
message when LCM is supported, because ClusterTransaction.message
does not have "cluster" attribute.

Change-Id: I1de41b819ade7d8c7ff467e5664b6f4c9bb295a3
Closes-Bug: #1571542

commit_message:
Install qemu-image from backports repo

qemu-image has been installed from testing to fix issues when
qemu-img can't convert image:
qemu-img: error writing zeroes at sector 0: Invalid argument

The issue has been fixed in qemu 2.2.0-rc2, reference [0].

Which has been added to debian backports.

This patch fixes issue with building coreos image, when qemu-utils
can't be installed from testing due to dependency problems.

Reference:
[0] http://git.qemu-project.org/?p=qemu.git;a=commitdiff;h=f3a9cfddae
[1] https://bugs.launchpad.net/cinder/+bug/1389728

Change-Id: Ie62a88e1d012aba1392b19c18137529c4c3ebf31
Related-Bug: #1490086
Closes-bug: #1570090
Closes-Bug: #1569835
(cherry picked from commit 52066d0a4920d2ccb3c6aef165e4a843ede4a809)

commit_message:
Add a vnic type for PF passthrough and a new libvirt vif driver

The new vnic type is defined by Neutron in the following change:

If1ab969c2002c649a3d51635ca2765c262e2d37f

We define it for Nova with this patch, and add a vif driver for plugging PFs -
it's really just a simple hostdev passthrough, which is already used so
we just abstract the code a bit.

The patch that same vif type to Neutron (it got overlooked by the
original work) is here:

https://review.openstack.org/262604

Change-Id: I1dc5601027ac97158d409d799b314a0c49968ce5
Related-blueprint: sriov-pf-passthrough-neutron-port
(cherry picked from commit 32069c8f397e395134c3b1142c2d852640685fef)

commit_message:
Add parameters verification when Audit is being created

We have to check Audit Type and Audit State to make sure
these parameters are in valid status.

Also, we provide default states for the next attributes:

- 'audit_template' is required and should be either UUID or text field
- 'state' is readonly so it raises an error if submitted in POST
  and is set by default to PENDING
- 'deadline' is optional and should be a datetime
- 'type' is a required text field

Change-Id: I2a7e0deec0ee2040e86400b500bb0efd8eade564
Closes-Bug: #1532843
Closes-Bug: #1533210

commit_message:
Remove eventlet support

Eventlet has been deprecated since the Kilo release and is
being removed in Newton.

A follow on patch will be proposed to remove the [ssl] section
since it is now redundant.

Co-Authored-By: Grzegorz Grasza <grzegorz.grasza@intel.com>
Partially implements: bp removed-as-of-newton

Change-Id: I963d94bbd188dbb6eba68623a42c5bc3f2289da4

commit_message:
Fix "Creates an agent build" parameters

"Creates an agent build" API supports multiple parameters on a request,
but api-ref doesn.t contain them at all This patch adds them.

The following JSON-Schema is for the API.
https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/api/openstack/compute/schemas/agents.py#L21

Part of bp:api-ref-in-rst

Change-Id: I4b026f691711b11c1918785dff89bf5196c7177d

commit_message:
Make HeatWorkers param affect the engine workers

With the addition of the num_engine_workers param in puppet-heat, we
can now wire the HeatWorkers parameter to also set that value, as
with the other workers.

Change-Id: I169b648737f797ccd45d12b66705d111e7b95bb7
Depends-On: I53a4333ca16df516294c733f85546c0b0a6a0b88

revisions:
[{'created': '2016-03-11 16:45:33.000000000', 'message': 'Use package-installs for undercloud elements

Ideally all elements would be using package-installs so we only
call yum once per stage, but since a lot of these elements are no
longer used this change focuses on just the elements doing one-off
package installs that I found in the undercloud install logs.

A follow-up change would be to do the same kind of audit for the
overcloud image build and fix up all of those elements.

Change-Id: Ie204c5d0aa0f48d3d93d834b51a644d8562cd2fd
'}]
commit_message:
Use package-installs for undercloud elements

Ideally all elements would be using package-installs so we only
call yum once per stage, but since a lot of these elements are no
longer used this change focuses on just the elements doing one-off
package installs that I found in the undercloud install logs.

A follow-up change would be to do the same kind of audit for the
overcloud image build and fix up all of those elements.

Change-Id: Ie204c5d0aa0f48d3d93d834b51a644d8562cd2fd

commit_message:
API for managing network groups

Individual network groups can be created, deleted and
modified. IP range management for each network is still
handled by the standard network_configuration API handlers.

Change-Id: I861485b5aebd8ae784fc71f405aab87e73f6d2e0
Implements: blueprint templates-for-networking

revisions:
[{'created': '2016-04-12 10:16:09.000000000', 'message': 'Notify resource_versions from agents only when needed

resource_versions were included into agent state reports recently to
support rolling upgrades (commit 97a272a892fcf488949eeec4959156618caccae8)
The downside is that it brought additional processing when handling state
reports on server side: update of local resources versions cache and
more seriously rpc casts to all other servers to do the same.
All this led to a visible performance degradation at scale with hundreds
of agents constantly sending reports. Under load (rally test) agents
may start "blinking" which makes cluster very unstable.

In fact there is no need to send and update resource_versions in each state
report. I see two cases when it should be done:
 1) agent was restarted (after it was upgraded);
 2) agent revived - which means that server was not receiving or being able
    to process state reports for some time (agent_down_time). During that
    time agent might be upgraded and restarted.

So this patch makes agents include resource_versions info only on startup.
After agent revival server itself will update version_manager with
resource_versions taken from agent DB record - this is to avoid
version_manager being outdated.

Closes-Bug: #1567497
Change-Id: I47a9869801f4e8f8af2a656749166b6fb49bcd3b
'}, {'created': '2016-04-12 10:17:01.000000000', 'message': 'Notify resource_versions from agents only when needed

resource_versions were included into agent state reports recently to
support rolling upgrades (commit 97a272a892fcf488949eeec4959156618caccae8)
The downside is that it brought additional processing when handling state
reports on server side: update of local resources versions cache and
more seriously rpc casts to all other servers to do the same.
All this led to a visible performance degradation at scale with hundreds
of agents constantly sending reports. Under load (rally test) agents
may start "blinking" which makes cluster very unstable.

In fact there is no need to send and update resource_versions in each state
report. I see two cases when it should be done:
 1) agent was restarted (after it was upgraded);
 2) agent revived - which means that server was not receiving or being able
    to process state reports for some time (agent_down_time). During that
    time agent might be upgraded and restarted.

So this patch makes agents include resource_versions info only on startup.
After agent revival server itself will update version_manager with
resource_versions taken from agent DB record - this is to avoid
version_manager being outdated.

Closes-Bug: #1567497
Change-Id: I47a9869801f4e8f8af2a656749166b6fb49bcd3b
(cherry picked from commit e532ee3fccd0820f9ab0efc417ee787fb8c870e9)

commit_message:
Notify resource_versions from agents only when needed

resource_versions were included into agent state reports recently to
support rolling upgrades (commit 97a272a892fcf488949eeec4959156618caccae8)
The downside is that it brought additional processing when handling state
reports on server side: update of local resources versions cache and
more seriously rpc casts to all other servers to do the same.
All this led to a visible performance degradation at scale with hundreds
of agents constantly sending reports. Under load (rally test) agents
may start "blinking" which makes cluster very unstable.

In fact there is no need to send and update resource_versions in each state
report. I see two cases when it should be done:
 1) agent was restarted (after it was upgraded);
 2) agent revived - which means that server was not receiving or being able
    to process state reports for some time (agent_down_time). During that
    time agent might be upgraded and restarted.

So this patch makes agents include resource_versions info only on startup.
After agent revival server itself will update version_manager with
resource_versions taken from agent DB record - this is to avoid
version_manager being outdated.

Closes-Bug: #1567497
Change-Id: I47a9869801f4e8f8af2a656749166b6fb49bcd3b
(cherry picked from commit e532ee3fccd0820f9ab0efc417ee787fb8c870e9)

commit_message:
Fix doc build if git is absent

When building packages if git is absent, then we should not set
html_last_updated_fmt. It can still be set via the -D switch
when building with sphinx-build.

Change-Id: I905736fc5f998385128b306c75bc8191b2797dc6
Closes-Bug: #1552251

commit_message:
Default caching to on for request-local caching.

Default cache to be enabled for request.local caching.
Since the default cache backend is dogpile.null, it is
safe to turn on caching by default. This will enable the
request_local caching for all deployments that do not
explicitly disable caching, thereby limiting the traffic
to the backends on a per-request basis.

With caching (in memcache) the addition of request local
cache was noticable (~10% inprovement), it stands to reason
that it will provide even more when it is offloading the
requests directly to SQL/LDAP.

Change-Id: I47d40c36799645d6fdd7b71e14e774ad75aa55f7

commit_message:
Fix foreignkey names of host/host_history table

The migration a54c57ada3f5_removes_useless_indexes.py doesn't set the
foreign key names like sqlalchemy_base.py.

This change fixes that.

Change-Id: I4d4c71e3462ee5581aab703592c225498102d6cd

commit_message:
Alarm-update failed with too few arguments

In monascaclient, alarm-update doesn't work because
one argument missing when calling  _send_alarm_event() function.

Also found a bug with the client in tempest. Change PATCH to PUT
for updating alarms

Change-Id: Ia83081f73de84cf28e4b2ffdc6ce451e0257ef55

building works.

http://logs.openstack.org/44/44654d5dd07104d6bda7bad24eaa8742c19697ec/post/networking-ovn-upstream-translation-update/d11ccac/

commit_message:
puppet/periodic: export ZUUL_REF

In puppet-openstack-integration-checkout JJB builder, make sure we
export ZUUL_REF, otherwise periodic jobs will fail with this error:

> Provide either ZUUL_REF or BRANCH in the calling enviromnent
> git failed, retrying

Change-Id: Iff99aec747cd778d559b5092d91a46ad24a5c975

commit_message:
Add to stackviz-export and stackviz-front docs

Adds additional information to the stackviz-export and stackviz-front
technical documents. Info about `stackviz-export` output files is
now included in the corresponding document. Directive and service
descriptions were added to stackviz-front, alongside inline comments
in the appropriate .js files.

Due to the unique structure of GitHub's RST renderer, includes will
no longer be used in the main README.

Change-Id: Iaebf1f1c3b5e4cbb4ea5e262f85672bc082bbe2f

commit_message:
Initialize neutron client with region name

All clients except neutron are initialized with region name.
This makes unable to use network related commands of
openstackclient in multi-region configurations

Change-Id: I200dc9a2f938c3e69357f91c79810df167e4fccb
Closes-bug: 1570491

commit_message:
Stop to wrap release_id into str

We have next commit in fuel-web https://review.openstack.org/#/c/303281/2
that add expectation  of int type of release_id.

In fuel-qa when we create cluster we get release id by release name
 and then cast it to string - that leads to 400
bad request with "message": "deque(['release']): u'2'
is not of type 'integer'", "errors": []}

Closes-Bug: #1571780
Change-Id: Ie894a056f33d770bebece4f4d24e3261b368c35a

commit_message:
Add debtcollector to requirements

debtcollector is used by oslo.db at runtime, but is not currently
mentioned in requirements.txt explicitly (which effectively means
it's installed as a transitive dependency now).

This fixes tox -epip-missing-reqs run. A follow up change to
project-config will make sure we run this check in the gate.

Closes-Bug: #1571739

Change-Id: I564030830708da5c8a18f0c8a127ae74d54ead39

[{'created': '2016-04-01 15:54:20.000000000', 'message': "ML2: update port's status to DOWN if its binding info has changed

ML2: update port's status to DOWN if its binding info has changed
This fixes the problem that when two or more ports in a network
are migrated to a host that did not previously have any ports in
the same network, the new host is sometimes not told about the
IP/MAC addresses of all the other ports in the network. In other
words, initial L2population does not work, for the new host.

This is because the l2pop mechanism driver only sends catch-up
information to the host when it thinks it is dealing with the first
active port on that host; and currently, when multiple ports are
migrated to a new host, there is always more than one active port so
the condition above is never triggered.

The fix is for the ML2 plugin to set a port's status to DOWN when
its binding info changes.

This patch also fixes the bug when nova thinks it should not wait
for any events from neutron because all ports are already active.

Closes-bug: #1483601
Closes-bug: #1443421

commit_message:
ML2: update port's status to DOWN if its binding info has changed

ML2: update port's status to DOWN if its binding info has changed
This fixes the problem that when two or more ports in a network
are migrated to a host that did not previously have any ports in
the same network, the new host is sometimes not told about the
IP/MAC addresses of all the other ports in the network. In other
words, initial L2population does not work, for the new host.

This is because the l2pop mechanism driver only sends catch-up
information to the host when it thinks it is dealing with the first
active port on that host; and currently, when multiple ports are
migrated to a new host, there is always more than one active port so
the condition above is never triggered.

The fix is for the ML2 plugin to set a port's status to DOWN when
its binding info changes.

This patch also fixes the bug when nova thinks it should not wait
for any events from neutron because all ports are already active.

Closes-bug: #1483601
Closes-bug: #1443421
Closes-Bug: #1522824
Related-Bug: #1450604
(cherry picked from commit c5fa665de3173f3ad82cc3e7624b5968bc52c08d)

Conflicts: neutron/plugins/ml2/drivers/l2pop/mech_driver.py

Change-Id: I342ad910360b21085316c25df2154854fd1001b2

commit_message:
Docs: Change invalid reference to FWaaS in VPNaaS documentation

In the VPNaaS section says that we must run
horizon playbook for updating horizon to
show the FWaaS panels, but here is the VPNaaS
panels.

Change-Id: I995148527dcb050358c6b3c6ea95c642ba987933

commit_message:
WIP: enforce domain_id upon project/group/user create

These resources are all domain scoped, thus should require the
domain id to be specified. We cannot assume or fallback on the
domain of the project scoped token, or the default domain.

Depends-On: I6004644531c2e86cafe3714451101e6b977a8593

Change-Id: Ic6d1a4df04a966974b5689acad6df576d341d191

commit_message:
Fix confusing naming in ldap EnableEmuMixin.

In keystone/common/ldap/core.py, the get_all() method of EnabledEmuMixIn is
using "tenant" as the return object. This is misleading as the core method
is not using as project only but also other identity or resources (such as
user and group). We should change to name to be more generic to avoid
confusion.

Change-Id: I53a7eb22539697e16ac9893daf59506483345f9e
closes-bug: 1571342

commit_message:
Clear DVR MAC on last agent deletion from host

Once all agents are deleted from a host, the DVR MAC generated
for that host should be deleted as well to prevent a buildup of
pointless flows generated in the OVS agent for hosts that don't
exist.

Closes-Bug: #1568206
Change-Id: I51e736aa0431980a595ecf810f148ca62d990d20

If no heat stack timeout is given, which happens quite commonly when

commit_message:
Don't show "None Minutes" if no stack timeout

If no heat stack timeout is given, which happens quite commonly when
launch stacks from the CLI, Horizon shows a Timeout of "None Minutes".
This is not correct and a bit non-sensical. A more clear value is simply
"None" for Timeout in this case.

Change-Id: Id4ea49f386a9d15c370a9b42147edb8082cf269f

commit_message:
Make queues lazy in subscriptions

Make queues lazy on operations with subscriptions, so the user will be
able to subscribe to yet unexisting queue.

blueprint lazy-queues-in-subscriptions

Change-Id: Ib5c25f160aa91525e18e9bbd06b6a48931ddec49

commit_message:
ML2: update port's status to DOWN if its binding info has changed

This fixes the problem that when two or more ports in a network
are migrated to a host that did not previously have any ports in
the same network, the new host is sometimes not told about the
IP/MAC addresses of all the other ports in the network. In other
words, initial L2population does not work, for the new host.

This is because the l2pop mechanism driver only sends catch-up
information to the host when it thinks it is dealing with the first
active port on that host; and currently, when multiple ports are
migrated to a new host, there is always more than one active port so
the condition above is never triggered.

The fix is for the ML2 plugin to set a port's status to DOWN when
its binding info changes.

This patch also fixes the bug when nova thinks it should not wait
for any events from neutron because all ports are already active.

Closes-bug: #1483601
Closes-bug: #1443421
Closes-Bug: #1522824
Related-Bug: #1450604
(cherry picked from commit c5fa665de3173f3ad82cc3e7624b5968bc52c08d)

Conflicts: neutron/plugins/ml2/drivers/l2pop/mech_driver.py

Change-Id: I342ad910360b21085316c25df2154854fd1001b2

devstack: Use magnum-api and magnum-cond for services

"m-api" is already used by Manila so switch to "magnum-api"
and "magnum-cond" for devstack.

revisions:
[{'created': '2016-04-18 15:22:24.000000000', 'message': 'Log copy for failed functional tests cannot be disabled

Setting the following in functional_creds.conf doesn't have any effect
for failed functional container tests:
    copy_logs = False

Description of changes/issues addressed:
- Client functional tests look in functional_creds.conf for the
  copy_logs setting while tempest/api tests look in tempest.conf.
  So an accessor method 'get_copy_logs' is added for BaseMagnumTest
  (for tempest tests), and this gets overridden by BaseMagnumClient.
- Call to lamda was missing an argument in copy_logs_handler.
- set_copy_logs in config.py was setting cls.copy logs inconsistently
  (sometimes boolean True, otherwise to a string).
- BaseMagnumClient was calling bool() on a string: "bool(copy_logs)".
  bool() on a string always returns True except for null string.

Change-Id: I234fd0433602914fdf03f04f2394f6dc802df4fd
Closes-Bug: #1570949
'}]
commit_message:
Log copy for failed functional tests cannot be disabled

Setting the following in functional_creds.conf doesn't have any effect
for failed functional container tests:
    copy_logs = False

Description of changes/issues addressed:
- Client functional tests look in functional_creds.conf for the
  copy_logs setting while tempest/api tests look in tempest.conf.
  So an accessor method 'get_copy_logs' is added for BaseMagnumTest
  (for tempest tests), and this gets overridden by BaseMagnumClient.
- Call to lamda was missing an argument in copy_logs_handler.
- set_copy_logs in config.py was setting cls.copy logs inconsistently
  (sometimes boolean True, otherwise to a string).
- BaseMagnumClient was calling bool() on a string: "bool(copy_logs)".
  bool() on a string always returns True except for null string.

Change-Id: I234fd0433602914fdf03f04f2394f6dc802df4fd
Closes-Bug: #1570949

commit_message:
hook up pci allocation for resizing

in API stage save a '_new' prefix flavor for pci devices,
then pci manager could allocate new devices based on new
instance type.

Wow, ok I used vagrant-swift-all-in-one's `autodoc` commands `doc` container to test this.

Normally listings are totally disabled, so if you visit `http://saio:8080/v1/AUTH_test/doc/` you get a 401.  Unless you explicitly disable web-mode-listings with `swift post doc -m Web-Listings:false` then you get a cutesy and helpful error message.  (N.B. the message doesn't show up if Web-Listings is empty).

The problem is that you still get the cute error page even if you totally disable public access to the container  (i.e. `swift post -r ''`)  :\

Further on master, even the helpful "you can enable web listing by setting X-Container-Meta-Web-Listings" copy is mis-leading since in that case you would *also* need to enable public access and listings ACL's `swift post doc -r '.r:*,.rlistings'`

On this brach everything works the same - except the helpful message doesn't show up unless you would have already been authorized for the listing and presented the normal xml response you generally expect from a '.r:*, .rlistings' container to begin with (e.g. had X-Container-Meta-Web-Listings not been set (i.e. `swift post doc -m Web-Listings:`) or if staticweb had not even been in the pipeline)

... which I think is a nice improvement.

I wasn't able to find any negative interaction with the Web-Index or Web-Error metadata items.'}, {'account_id': 6968, 'date': '2015-11-24 11:07:10.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

The idea sounds good to me; however there is a small problem with this change: if the container is public, and web-listings is set to False you get a 401, which seems wrong:

 swift post -r ".r:*,.rlistings" doc
 swift post doc -m Web-Listings:false
 curl -v http://saio:8080/v1/AUTH_test/doc/

I think this is not intended?'}, {'account_id': 1179, 'date': '2015-11-24 18:30:06.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: -Code-Review

so that's basically exactly opposite of what I thought I observed yesterday - maybe I was switching branches and forgot to restart the proxy - or some other mistake.  I'm trying again now.

Thanks @cschwede!"}, {'account_id': 1179, 'date': '2015-11-24 18:56:04.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 1179, 'date': '2015-11-24 19:00:36.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

So, basically that authorize callback is totally dependent on if the req param has the acl attribute populated - which is normally done by the GETorHEAD_base method in the ContainerController.

I don't see a good way to decide if a request to list the container is going to be authorized or not other than making the request - which is exactly what would happen anyway if you sent X-Web-Mode: false or didn't have any of the staticweb headers on the container.

So I say we make the listing request and let it error if it's going to - and only after we have a successful listing in-hand we decide if static web wants to reject it and display it's custom Web-Listing: false error message.

I think this change does that.

I had to fix up a test that was missing a stub response because the code is now making the request regardless of the container metadata."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-11-24 20:07:47.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified+1

Thanks Christian for spotting the flaw and thanks Clay for diagnosing. I agree, without the read acl set in the request the the call from staticweb to swift.authorize will return an incorrect deny response.

However, it turns out that staticweb already has the read_acl available from an earlier call to get_container_info! So we don't need to make the full listing request again.

While playing with this I also uncovered a couple more ways in which container existence can be revealed (updated on bug report). So this version changes version *1* in two ways:

1. set the read acl in the request before calling swift.authorize

2. move the callback to swift.authorize earlier in container handling

And here is the behaviour I see with this version: https://gist.github.com/alistairncoles/aec83966658c14bd3dca


You may feel that step 2 is going too far in terms of changing what clients experience form staticweb. If so I will move the call back. But I'm currently thinking that if the request is not auth'd then static web should not be handling it."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-11-25 19:46:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified+1

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-11-23 18:29:53.000000000', 'message': "Stop staticweb revealing container existence to unauth'd requests

When a container has `X-Container-Meta-Web-Listings: false` then
staticweb will return a 404 in response to a GET or HEAD on the
container, regardless of whether the request is auth'd. That provides
a way to probe for container existence. It should return a 401 if the
request is not auth'd.

This patch adds a call to swift.authorize before returning the 404.

Change-Id: I382323b49dc8f6d67bf4494db7084a860a10db59
Closes-Bug: 1506116
"}, {'created': '2015-11-24 18:56:04.000000000', 'message': "Stop staticweb revealing container existence to unauth'd requests

When a container has `X-Container-Meta-Web-Listings: false` then
staticweb will return a 404 in response to a GET or HEAD on the

commit_message:
Stop staticweb revealing container existence to unauth'd requests

When a container has `X-Container-Meta-Web-Listings: false` then
staticweb will return a 404 in response to a GET or HEAD on the
container, regardless of whether the request is auth'd. That provides
a way to probe for container existence. It should return a 401 if the
request is not auth'd.

This patch adds a call to swift.authorize before returning the 404.

Closes-Bug: 1506116
Change-Id: I382323b49dc8f6d67bf4494db7084a860a10db59

commit_message:
Totally drop Qpid support

Qpid was removed in Mitaka from Oslo Messaging, so now we can
drop it in manifests.

Change-Id: Id23736218e97cb19fd009850e35859c1a94801e4

subject: Totally drop Qpid support

Totally drop Qpid support

Qpid was removed in Mitaka from Oslo Messaging, so now we can
drop it in manifests.

Change-Id: Ica56c344fac4505ebdf8c739334c9b0400a02c87

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

    IRC: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/IRC

According to the documentation[0], structured facts were added to facter 2.0. We currently run facter 1.7.x. While it does technically support external structured facts[1], I could never get it to work correctly in testing.

Also they are not enabled by default with 2.0 (see [0]). This is why this is a comma separated fact.

[0] https://docs.puppetlabs.com/facter/2.0/fact_overview.html#writing-structured-facts
[1] https://docs.puppetlabs.com/facter/1.7/release_notes.html#external-facts'}, {'account_id': 13948, 'date': '2015-09-30 06:29:24.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

The stringify_facts option is actually enabled since at least 3.4 we're currently using[1]. It just isn't the default option for facter itself. I can't make noop tests work through, so I'll probably leave this change with Workflow -1, as puppet 3.8 and facter 2.4 are expected to hit Fuel repositories in a week[2].


[1] https://docs.puppetlabs.com/references/3.4.2/configuration.html#stringifyfacts
[2] https://bugs.launchpad.net/fuel/+bug/1500414"}, {'account_id': 13948, 'date': '2015-09-30 08:34:16.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-09-30 08:34:30.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified+1

[WIP] Upstream CentOS on MOS-7 master node

MOS-7 master nodes with upstream CentOS-6.

Totally drop Qpid support

drop it in manifests.

drop it in manifests.

commit_message:
Notify Heat only if kube-apiserver is running

Kubernetes bay needs to be fully functional before notifying Heat
to bring the stack to CREATE_COMPLETE. This patch added a systemd
unit that keeps pinging the kube-apiserver and notify Heat once
it goes through.

Change-Id: Ib4fb22f3040d76d488c6cac6873d64b4d973ebb1
Closes-Bug: #1551824

commit_message:
[install] cleanup keystone apache config for ubuntu, suse, and rdo

Apache 2.4 is part of Ubuntu 14.04, openSUSE Leap 42.1, SLES 12,
RHEL/CentOS 7, and Fedora 23.

No need to check for versions < 2.4.

Change-Id: I70cb0a3a6a23d763cc1300097a94bed2435f6d06

commit_message:
Python3: Add support for iter.next

Replaced iter.next() with next(iter)

This patch is generated by the following tool using
'next' option.

https://github.com/haypo/sixer
Command:
python sixer.py -w 'next' trove/

Partially implements: blueprint trove-python3

Change-Id: Ifbe25ddaa20f60b8af245f4745a9851c9b262bf3

[{'created': '2016-04-15 17:56:55.000000000', 'message': "Fix Infra docs layout: remove redundant Zabbix

Because of (probable) copy-pasting error Zabbix server section is twice
present in Index menu. Zabbix server deployment section is a part of Fuel
Infrastructure docs, so it shouldn't be visible on the topt level.

Closes-Bug: 1568880

Change-Id: I9966a33d150b3766fde18d248919433e13fe1616
Signed-off-by: Lesya Novaselskaya <onovaselskaya@mirantis.com>
"}]
commit_message:
Fix Infra docs layout: remove redundant Zabbix

Because of (probable) copy-pasting error Zabbix server section is twice
present in Index menu. Zabbix server deployment section is a part of Fuel
Infrastructure docs, so it shouldn't be visible on the topt level.

Closes-Bug: 1568880

Change-Id: I9966a33d150b3766fde18d248919433e13fe1616
Signed-off-by: Lesya Novaselskaya <onovaselskaya@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Clarify role documentation and remove duplication

The README now makes clear that MongoDB is a dependency
and the role doc itself now simply includes the README
instead of duplicating its content.

Change-Id: I4f5008166ad385619ee50486aa953a4a7dec6f3c

commit_message:
Fix container-create memory not passed

Commit I34e5e49ae650219f986a2b0032df65672c319ec6 tried to fix mem_limit
not passed to docker when create container for docker API vesion >=1.19
in a wrong way, this patch fixes it by passing Memory unit to host_config

Closes-Bug: #1567834
Change-Id: Id8da5e40cf165317a9a5453036490cc028bd2e0d
Co-Authored-By: Spyros Trigazis <strigazi@gmail.com>

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

    IRC: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/IRC
    Workflow: http://docs.openstack.org/infra/manual/developers.html
    Commit Messages: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/GitCommitMessages"}, {'account_id': 11928, 'date': '2016-04-18 09:22:19.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2: Commit message was updated.'}, {'account_id': 5707, 'date': '2016-04-18 10:21:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2016-04-18 10:22:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified-1

commit_message:
Typo in sysctl command example Edit

Fixes error:

    # sysctl -w 'sys.net.ipv4.ip_local_reserved_ports=35357'
    sysctl: cannot stat /proc/sys/sys/net/ipv4/ip_local_reserved_ports: No such file or directory

The new command works:

    # sysctl -w 'net.ipv4.ip_local_reserved_ports=35357'
    net.ipv4.ip_local_reserved_ports = 35357

Closes-Bug: #1571555
Change-Id: I9665f56c23f50d45e4303f78046dc46becb59ec5

commit_message:
crypto - verify that x-object-meta-etag does not confuse

The TODO being removed was valid when we were using
x-object-sysmeta-crypto namespace to store user
metadata crypto-meta. But now we have x-object-transient-sysmeta-
the concern is gone. Adds a test to verify that x-object-meta-etag
sent by the client does not result in confused crypto meta headers.

Change-Id: I531e048645f6e01bc172fa8c44f11ec0354bf7f3

commit_message:
XenAPI: Minor update about Kronos and XenAPI

* Kronos section should be removed as it is deprecated
* xenserver-core should be removed as it is not in use
* Add a note that only XenAPI needs the Compute service in a domU

Change-Id: Ieef5e074534bfc03e2369f2fdf65ce6590f1d79e
